    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense faces a challenging slate today, highlighted by a difficult matchup against Zack Wheeler, though our top-tier assets remain positioned for high-output performances. **Kyle Tucker** (76.51) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.76) lead the charge as our strongest plays, benefiting significantly from favorable park factors and the current wind-out conditions. While **Jackson Merrill** draws a tough assignment against Gallen, his dynamic platoon advantage propels him to elite status. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45) provides a massive anchor in the utility spot; his elite xwOBA of .384 and a strong platoon edge against Cantillo make him an indispensable piece for today\u2019s 5x5 rotation, despite the moderate xERA of the opposing starter.\n\nStrategic lineup construction forced a difficult decision regarding **Marcell Ozuna** (48.31), who serves as our most notable bench casualty. Despite a solid projection, **Marcell Ozuna** fell just short of the efficiency threshold required to displace starters like **Dominic Smith** (41.10) or **Heliot Ramos** (46.95), the latter of whom gains a slight bump in stolen base potential due to the opposing pitcher\u2019s slower delivery. Risk management remains centered on the uncertain lineup statuses for **Drake Baldwin**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Dominic Smith**. We are particularly monitoring the matchup for **Drake Baldwin** and **Dominic Smith** against the elite arm of Zack Wheeler; while their scores are currently viable, Wheeler\u2019s 2.73 xERA imposes a significant drag on their efficiency, keeping their upside capped compared to the rest of the roster.",
